exports[`characterize: multi-subject (2 people) cartoon, no brand, caricature mode 1`] = `
"Transform this photo into a 3D animated character portrait in the style of Pixar and Disney Animation Studios (The Incredibles, Coco, Up, Brave). Do not add anyone not in the original photo.\\n\\nPreserve accurately: skin tone, eye color, hair color, hairstyle, facial hair, glasses, jewelry, clothing, and any visible accessories or distinguishing features. The portrait must be immediately recognizable as the same person.\\n\\nStyle: High-quality Pixar-style 3D render with warm, rich color grading. Big round expressive eyes with detailed iris reflections, soft rounded features with a touch of stylization. Smooth subsurface scattering on skin for that signature Pixar porcelain glow. Rich fabric and hair textures with individual strand detail. Every surface should have the polished, tactile quality of a Pixar film frame.\\n\\nBody proportions: Keep the body realistically proportioned — normal adult height, limbs, and torso like The Incredibles characters. Do NOT make the body short, stocky, or compressed. The face and head can be slightly stylized but the body should look natural and well-proportioned.\\n\\nLighting: Warm cinematic Pixar-style lighting — soft key light with golden tones, gentle fill light, and a subtle cool rim light. Soft ambient occlusion in creases and under the chin.\\n\\nComposition: Frame from the waist up. Give them a warm, friendly expression.\\nThis photo has exactly 2 HUMAN subjects. Include ALL of them positioned as shown. The output must contain exactly 2 people — no more, no fewer.\\nBackground: Recreate the background from the original photo in the same art style. Keep it natural and consistent with the scene.\\n\\nIMPORTANT: This has multiple people. Transform each person into a WILDLY EXAGGERATED CARICATURE — giant heads on tiny bodies, comically oversized eyes, enormous grins, bobblehead proportions. Push the abstraction as far as possible while keeping each person vaguely identifiable by their most obvious trait (hair color, glasses, beard, etc.). This should look like a theme-park caricature artist on overdrive — NOT a realistic portrait. Prioritize humor, energy, and bold graphic style over any attempt at photographic likeness. Do NOT try to make the faces look realistic.\\n\\nFINAL REMINDER: Exactly 2 humans in the output — no more, no fewer."
`;

